org.openbel.framework.api
Class Resolver

java.lang.Object
  org.openbel.framework.api.Resolver

public class Resolver
extends Object

Resolver defines a utility to resolve BEL expressions to elements within a specific Kam.

BelTerm expressions can be resolved to Kam.KamNode elements within a specific Kam.

Edges in the form (subject BelTerm, Relationship, object BelTerm) can also be resolved to Kam.KamEdge elements within a specific Kam. This implementation relies on resolving both the subject and object BelTerm to Kam.KamNode elements.

Author:
Anthony Bargnesi <abargnesi@selventa.com>

                           String belTerm)
                    throws ParseException,

Resolves a BelTerm, as a String, to an equivalent Kam.KamNode in the Kam.

Parameters:
kam - Kam, the KAM to resolve against
kamStore - KAMStore, the KAM store to use in resolving the bel term expression
belTerm - String, the BelTerm string, which cannot be null or the empty string
Returns:
the resolved Kam.KamNode for the BelTerm, or null if one could not be found
Throws:
InvalidArgument - Thrown if kam, kamStore, or belTerm is null
ParseException - Thrown if belTerm cannot be parsed to a valid BEL term expression
ResolverException - Thrown if an error occurred resolving the BelTerm using the KAMStore

resolve

public Kam.KamEdge resolve(Kam kam,
                           KamStore kamStore,
                           String subjectBelTerm,
                           RelationshipType rtype,
                           String objectBelTerm)
                    throws ResolverException,
                           ParseException
Resolves a subject BelTerm, relationship type, and object BelTerm to a Kam.KamEdge, if it exists within the Kam. If it does not exist then a null is returned.

This resolve operation must resolve both the subjectBelTerm and objectBelTerm to a Kam.KamNode in order to find a Kam.KamEdge.

Parameters:
kam - Kam, the kam to resolve into, which cannot be null
kamStore - KAMStore, the KAM store to use in resolving the BelTerms and Edge, which cannot be null
subjectBelTerm - String, the subject BelTerm to resolve to a Kam.KamNode, which cannot be null
rtype - RelationshipType, the relationship type of the edge to resolve, which cannot be null
objectBelTerm - String, the object BelTerm to resolve to a Kam.KamNode, which cannot be null
Returns:
the resolved Kam.KamEdge in kam, or null if the edge does not exist
Throws:
InvalidArgument - Thrown if kam, kamStore, subjectBelTerm, rtype, or objectBelTerm is null
ResolverException - Thrown if an error occurred resolving the BelTerm using the KAMStore
ParseException - Thrown if subjectBelTerm or objectBelTerm cannot be parsed to a valid BEL term expression
